cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks and proposes a method to reduce the number of parameters in convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of regularization and the linear combination of filters, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The proposed method involves the use of orthogonal filters, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the computational requirements of the proposed method, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
